# Environment Configuration Examples

## Local Development
```
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=5000
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:./db.sqlite
JWT_SECRET=dev-secret-key-change-this
SESSION_SECRET=dev-session-secret-change-this
UPLOADS_DIR=./uploads
DOMAIN=localhost:5000
```

## Production (VPS/Docker)
```
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:/app/db.sqlite
JWT_SECRET=<generate-secure-random-string-64-chars>
SESSION_SECRET=<generate-secure-random-string-64-chars>
UPLOADS_DIR=/app/uploads
DOMAIN=your-domain.com
```

## Production (with PostgreSQL)
```
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@postgres-host:5432/elvision
JWT_SECRET=<generate-secure-random-string-64-chars>
SESSION_SECRET=<generate-secure-random-string-64-chars>
UPLOADS_DIR=/app/uploads
DOMAIN=your-domain.com
```

## Generate Secure Secrets
Run this command to generate secure random strings:
```bash
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

## Frontend Environment (if deploying to Vercel)
```
VITE_API_URL=https://api.your-domain.com
VITE_WS_URL=wss://api.your-domain.com
```

Or for local development:
```
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
VITE_WS_URL=ws://localhost:5000
```
